he CMB Planck maps on so called\nGASS field covering an area of 11% in the southern hemisphere. We find that\nwith such a small sky fraction and dust residuals present in CIB maps, we do\nnot detect ISW signal and the measured signal is consistent with zero. In order\nnot to degrade the SNR for the ISW measurement by more than 10% on the 40% sky,\nwe find that the dust needs to be cleaned up to 0.01% level on the power\nspectrum.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 12 Sep 2018 16:43:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-06-03"}
